**Event Title:** REG - Scholarships - SAINTCON

**Event Description:**
The UtahSAINT Organization announces the Conference Scholarship Program designed to support talented and promising "hackers" in participating in the SAINTCON event. For SAINTCON 2023, up to 20 scholarships will be offered.

**Application Status:**
Scholarship applications have closed.

**Scholarship Program Overview:**
- The program aims to assist individuals facing financial barriers to attend the conference.
- Scholarships are awarded on an individual basis; no group applications.
- It is advised to reach out for consideration if there is a student or group deserving special attention.

**Criteria and Qualifications:**
- Applicants must be at least 14 years old.
- Applicants under 18 must be accompanied by an adult attendee who is not reliant on a scholarship.
- Applicants must not be currently employed by an organization that pays for conference entry.
- An essay submission is required.

**Included in the Scholarship Award:**
- Free pass to the conference.
- Conference-provided lunches and snacks.

**Not Included in the Scholarship Award:**
- Travel expenses, hotel accommodations, additional meals, and other incurred costs.

**Award Process:**
- Submissions reviewed by a panel of security professionals.
- Notifications sent to the registered email addresses with registration codes for free registration.
- Incomplete applications will be disqualified but can be re-submitted.

**Terms and Conditions:**
- Awardees must register within seven days of notification.
- Scholarship tickets are non-transferable and must be used by the awarded applicant.
- Awardees must notify the registration team if they can no longer attend. 

**Website Links:**
- Event Website: [SAINTCON](https://saintcon.org)
- FAQ: [Frequently Asked Questions](https://saintcon.org/faq)
- Code of Conduct: [Code of Conduct](https://saintcon.org/coc) 

**Contact Information:**
For further inquiries or support regarding the scholarship application, attendees are encouraged to refer to the provided support links on the event website.